Barrelheat_TopMessage: This page allows you to lookup Barrel Heat data.
Barrelheat_NoteMsg: Click to identify the barrel heater as GREEN = FUNCTIONAL and RED = SUSPECT
Barrelheat_NoteMsg2: Increase barrel heaters 35 degrees per zone and check with a surface pyrometer </br> Increase all zones on the barrel by 35 degrees.Wait 2-3 min and use a surface pryometer to get a reading off each heater band. Bad Heaterbands will show a temp close to your original setpoint. Heaters that are working will be 35°C - 70°C degrees higher in temp.</br> Example:</br>Barrel is set at 200°C. Increase to 240°C. Heaters bands that aren't working will be at 175°C. </br>Heaters that are working will read 240°C - 280°C

GateSeal_TopMessage: This page allows you to lookup Gate Seal data.
GateSeal_Discription: Description </br> 1. Choose a start point in the seconds to start your study </br> 2. Pack/Hold Time needs to be set to the same psi </br> 3. Preferably set pack time to zero and only use hold timer </br> 4. Weigh each shot.  Separate runners from the part </br> 5. DO NOT INCLUDE RUNNER IN YOUR PART WEIGHT !! </br> 6. Gate Increase pack/hold time by 1 sec and repeat </br> 7. Gate Seal Study is complete once the part weight does not increase Part weights can be in grams, lbs, oz Graphs looks best in lbs
GateSeal_Note: NOTE: DO NOT INCLUDE RUNNER IN YOUR PART WEIGHT

ConversionTools_PreNotes: Pre-Production molds are new molds within IAC.  First shots on the mold will be called T-0 with T-1, T-2, etc following until the mold is shipped to its production plant.  The pre-production area will contain part and process information from every sample.  Conversion tools are contained in this area for position and pressure transfers when moved to a different molding machine.
ConversionTools_PostNotes: Production molds are current running, established molds within IAC.  The production area has tools available to keep process history, machine setups, and tools for converting position and pressure when a mold is transfer into another machine.
